 To solve this problem, we can first rewrite $6^{12}$ and $36^5$ using prime factorization. We have $6^{12} = (2 \times 3)^{12}$ and $36^5 = (2^2 \times 3^2)^5$. Using the properties of exponents, we can simplify each term:
\begin{align*}
6^{12} &= (2 \times 3)^{12} \\
&= 2^{12} \times 3^{12}
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
36^5 &= (2^2 \times 3^2)^5 \\
&= (2^2)^5 \times (3^2)^5 \\
&= 2^{10} \times 3^{10}
\end{align*}
Next, we can divide $6^{12}$ by $36^5$:
\begin{align*}
\frac{6^{12}}{36^5} &= \frac{2^{12} \times 3^{12}}{2^{10} \times 3^{10}} \\
&= \frac{2^{12-10} \times 3^{12-10}}{1} \\
&= \frac{2^2 \times 3^2}{1} \\
&= 2^2 \times 3^2 \\
&= 4 \times 9 \\
&= 36
\end{align*}
Therefore, $6^{12} \div 36^5 = \boxed{36}$.
