 Let $\omega$ be a $16$th root of unity. Then \begin{align*}
\left.\frac{d^{3}}{dx^{3}}\prod\limits_{k = 1}^{16}(1-kx) \right|_{x = 0} &= (-1)^316\left.\sum_{\substack{S\subset\{1,\ldots,16\} \\  |S| = 3}}\prod_{k\notin S}k\right| \\ &= \sum_{\substack{S\subset\{1,\ldots,16\} \\  |S| = 3}}\prod_{k\notin S}k \\ &= \sum_{\substack{S\subset\{1,\ldots,16\} \\  |S| = 3}}\prod_{k\in S}(-k) \\ &= -\left(\sum_{k = 1}^{16}k\right)\left(\sum_{\substack{m+n+p = 16 \\  1\leqslant m\leqslant p}}mp\right) \\ &= -\left(\frac{16\cdot 17}{2}\right)\sum_{k = 1}^{14}k\cdot 2k \\ &= -\left(\frac{16\cdot 17 \cdot 14}{2}\right)(14!). \end{align*}
Therefore, the coefficient of $x^2$ is $\boxed{-2 \cdot 14 \cdot 15 \cdot 16 \cdot 14!}$. 
